[Median of a Triangle]
A line segment connecting any vertex of a triangle to the midpoint of the
opposite side of the triangle.

Every triangle has 3 medians (a median for every midpoint).

[Centroid of a Triangle]
The point in a triangle where the three medians meet. This point is also the
center of mass for the triangle.

It divides a median into two segments where the ratio of the lengths is 2:1.
The endpoints of the larger segment are the vertex and the centroid. The
endpoints of the smaller segment are the midpoint of the opposite side and
the centroid.

