Segment RW is a median of triangle RST.
X is the centroid of RST.
What is the length of segment RW?

y.......................
XW = RW / 2
y + 7 = 2(2y - 1) / 2
y + 7 = 2y - 1
y + 8 = 2y
8 = y

RW......................
RW = RX + XW
RW = 2(2y - 1) + y + 7
RW = 4y - 2 + y + 7
RW = 5y - 2 + 7
RW = 5y + 5
RW = 5(8) + 5
RW = 40 + 5
RW = 45

RW (alt)................
RW = 3(XW)
RW = 3(y + 7)
RW = 3y + 21
RW = 24 + 21
RW = 45

